Class GroupByCountPair

  • java.lang.Object
    • csc555.ebratt.depaul.edu.GroupByCountPair
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<GroupByCountPair>, org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable, org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable<GroupByCountPair>

    public class GroupByCountPair
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable, org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable<GroupByCountPair>
    GroupByCountPair is a class that allows for secondary sorting in a hadoop framework. It works on Text and LongWritable objects under the assumption that the user wants to group by and count to be something that cane be sorted.

    11/11/2015

        public int compareTo(GroupByCountPair in)
        Compares two GroupByCountPair objects and sorts them by count in a descending fashion. So, for example, "subreddit_1" and "subreddit_2" would be sorted as "subreddit_2", "subreddit_1".
